   </div>

   <div class="main_section">
      <div class="sub_section">
         <h3>Using the Speck App</h3>
         <div>
            <p>
               The following videos demonstrate the various features of the Speck app in detail.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row sub_section">
         <div class="col-sm-7">
            <a name="overview" class="anchor"></a>
            <h4>Speck App Overview</h4>
            <p>
               This video gives a brief overview of the various features of the Speck app including changing the Speck's
               palette and value scale, changing the sample interval, deleting data and resetting settings, configuring
               Wi-Fi, and setting up uploads.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div class="col-sm-5">
            {{> vimeo_video_thumbnail_with_caption videoId="129042696" title="Speck App: Overview" caption="Speck App Overview" thumbnailImageFilename="520389907_640.jpg"}}
         </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row sub_section">
         <div class="col-sm-7">
            <a name="downloading-data" class="anchor"></a>
            <h4>Downloading Data Samples</h4>
            <p>
               To download saved data samples from your Speck to your computer, do the following:
            </p>
            <ol>
               <li>On the Speck app, choose the "Download Data" option.</li>
               <li>Assign a filename and download location, and choose "Save."</li>
               <li>Once all data samples have been downloaded, choose "Stop Downloading."</li>
               <li>The data file is a plain-text CSV file, thus you can open it with your favorite text editor.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>
               This video demonstrates how to download saved data samples from your Speck to your computer.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div class="col-sm-5">
            {{> vimeo_video_thumbnail_with_caption videoId="129042974" title="Speck App: Downloading Data Samples" caption="Downloading Data Samples" thumbnailImageFilename="520424514_640.jpg"}}
         </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row sub_section">
         <div class="col-sm-7">
            <a name="settings" class="anchor"></a>
            <h4>Settings</h4>
            <p>
               This video demonstrates the features within Settings tab, including how to do the following:
            </p>
            <ul>
               <li>Change the rate at which the Speck will save data samples to its memory.</li>
               <li>Delete all data from your Speck</li>
               <li>Deactivate data uploads to specksensor.com</li>
               <li>Reset all of the Speck's settings to the factory defaults.</li>
            </ul>
         </div>
         <div class="col-sm-5">
            {{> vimeo_video_thumbnail_with_caption videoId="129043524" title="Speck App: Settings" caption="Settings" thumbnailImageFilename="521301065_640.jpg"}}
         </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row sub_section">
         <div class="col-sm-7">
            <a name="wireless-networking" class="anchor"></a>
            <h4>Wireless Networking Configuration</h4>
            <p>
               To configure your Speck for Wi-Fi, do the following:
            </p>
            <ol>
               <li>On the Wi-Fi tab, click the "Scan for WiFi Networks" button.</li>
               <li>Click on the name of your network, and type in a network password if needed.</li>
               <li>Check to make sure the WiFi icon appears on your Speck screen. Please be patient, it's normal for the Speck to take 20 seconds or so to connect.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>
               This video demonstrates configuring a Speck for a Wi-Fi network.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div class="col-sm-5">
            {{> vimeo_video_thumbnail_with_caption videoId="129066394" title="Speck App: Wireless Networking Configuration" caption="Wireless Networking Configuration" thumbnailImageFilename="520424641_640.jpg"}}
         </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row sub_section">
         <div class="col-sm-7">
            <a name="upload-configuration" class="anchor"></a>
            <h4>Upload Configuration</h4>
            <p>
               To configure your Speck to upload its data to your account on specksensor.com, do the following:
            </p>
            <ol>
               <li>Ensure you have the Speck configured to Wi-Fi.</li>
               <li>Click on the Upload Configuration icon on your Speck app.</li>
               <li>Login using the email and password used when you created your specksensor.com account, or sign up for a new account if you have not yet created one.</li>
               <li>On the Registration tab, create a custom name for your Speck, and complete by clicking "Register."</li>
               <li>On the Location Info tab, name the location of your Speck and complete by using the map to geolocate your Speck.</li>
               <li>
                  Please be aware that the Speck will not attempt to upload data samples while the Speck app is running
                  and connected to the Speck, so quit the app when you have finished configuring and are ready for
                  uploads to begin.
               </li>
            </ol>
            <p>
               This video demonstrates configuring a Speck for uploads.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div class="col-sm-5">
            {{> vimeo_video_thumbnail_with_caption videoId="129067639" title="Speck App: Upload Configuration" caption="Upload Configuration" thumbnailImageFilename="520425452_640.jpg"}}
         </div>
